        "prompt_mode": "no_prompt",
        "prompt_sha256": null,
        "transcript": "It grew louder, louder, louder, and still the men chatted pleasantly and smiled. Was it possible they heard not? Almighty God, no, no, they heard they suspected they knew they were making a mockery of my horror this I thought and this I think. But anything was better than this agony, anything was more tolerable than this derision, I could bear those hypocritical smiles no longer. I felt that I must scream or die, and now, again, hark, louder, louder, louder, louder. Villains, I shrieked, dissemble no more. I admit the deed tear up the planks here, here it is the beating of his hideous heart. Thanks for watching.",
